        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/john_morris/{size}/840_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-11-28T14:54:34.757Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Grand_Cru_Cru\" data-username=\"Mark_Golodetz\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"291836\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mark_golodetz/48/76850_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Mark_Golodetz:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The Du Tertre 1979 was a sleeper at the time, and the geeks who know are constantly on the hunt for it. With good reason. Some of the power has gone, but there is a beautiful fruit component, leather and the beginnings of earth and forest floor. Although no great hurry, it is probably time to starting to drink them up, as it won\u2019t get better. 94</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I guess it\u2019s dating myself to say that I remember what a sleeper this was. Nice to hear it\u2019s still motoring along nicely.</p>",
